  abstract = {Simultaneous recordings of thousands of extracellular spikes are now possible, using silicon-based recording devices with large numbers of electrode contacts, such as high-density multi-electrode arrays (MEA) or multi-shank laminar electrodes. With the associated increase of data amounts and complexity in such recordings, manual spike sorting is not viable. Hence, there is a dire need for validated automated spike sorting methods, able to correctly resolve spikes of single neurons, as recently reviewed [1]. \\
 \\
